<subSubSection id="C35B6510FFD1FFDF5D37FE33B4E8F93D" lastPageId="61" lastPageNumber="619" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD1FFDE5D37FE33B0B2FCA2" blockId="60.[826,1441,412,801]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37FE33B095FE32" box="[826,1414,412,434]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
Biology and host plant associations: 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5AEDFE33B095FE32" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[1248,1414,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Myrmecophyes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is found almost exclusively on grasses. In the 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFD1FFDE5B68FE14B08EFE53" box="[1381,1437,443,464]" name="United States of America" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">USA</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5D37FE75B6EFFE6C" box="[826,1020,474,495]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orgenonensis">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37FE75B6EFFE6C" box="[826,1020,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">My. orgenonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected from 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5B18FE75B69EFD8E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="idahoensis">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5B18FE75B69EFD8E" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Festuca idahoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DDBFE57B66FFDAE" authority="(Schuh &amp; Lattin, 1980)" baseAuthorityName="Schuh &amp; Lattin" baseAuthorityYear="1980" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agropyron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicatum">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5DDBFE57B1D0FD8E" box="[982,1219,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Agropyron spicatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5AD4FE57B667FDAE" author="Schuh RT &amp; Lattin JD" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref49067" refString="Schuh RT, Lattin JD. 1980. Myrmecophyes oregonensis, a new species of Halticini (Hemiptera, Miridae) from the western United States. American Museum Novitates, 2697: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Schuh &amp; Lattin, 1980</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D85FDB9B1F3FDAF" author="Kerzhner IM &amp; Yachevskii TL" box="[904,1248,534,556]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="851 - 1118" refId="ref45948" refString="Kerzhner IM, Yachevskii TL. 1967. Order Hemiptera (Heteroptera). In: Bei-Bienko GY, ed. Keys to the insects of the European USSR. Vol 1. Apterygota, Paleoptera, Hemimetabola. Moskva, Leningrad: Zoological Institute, USSR Academy of Sciences, 851 - 1118." type="book chapter" year="1967">Kerzhner &amp; Yachevskii (1967)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5B5EFDB8B6B8FDC9" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboornatus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5B5EFDB8B6B8FDC9" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">My. alboornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DE4FD9AB18CFDC8" box="[1001,1183,565,587]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agropyron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5DE4FD9AB14CFDC9" box="[1001,1119,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Agropyron</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
in Eastern (former) USSR; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D98FDFBB121FDE9" author="Bykov AA" box="[917,1074,596,618]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="495 - 501" refId="ref42447" refString="Bykov AA. 1971. Mirid bugs of the genus Myrmecophyes Fieb. (Heteroptera, Miridae) in the fauna of the Tien-Shan and the Pamir-Alai. Entomological Review 50: 495 - 501." type="journal article" year="1971">Bykov (1971)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5ABCFDFBB064FDEA" authorityName="Horvath" authorityYear="1926" box="[1201,1399,596,617]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrotrichus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5ABCFDFBB064FDEA" box="[1201,1399,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">My. macrotrichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5D37FDDCB682FD0B" box="[826,913,627,648]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37FDDCB682FD0B" box="[826,913,627,648]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Festuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DDFFDDCB143FD0B" box="[978,1104,627,648]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5DDFFDDCB107FD0B" box="[978,1044,627,648]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Carex</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A98FDDCB03EFD04" authorityName="Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner" authorityYear="2000" box="[1173,1325,626,648]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontosus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5A98FDDCB03EFD04" box="[1173,1325,626,648]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">My. frontosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected from 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A0FFD3EB00EFD25" box="[1026,1309,657,678]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Psathyrostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="juncea">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5A0FFD3EB00EFD25" box="[1026,1309,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Psathyrostachys juncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5B31FD3EB08AFD24" authorityName="Ehanno" authorityYear="1960" box="[1340,1433,657,679]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D4FFD00B18EFD45" author="Drapolyuk IS &amp; Kerzhner IM" box="[834,1181,687,710]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="301 - 305" refId="ref43521" refString="Drapolyuk IS, Kerzhner IM. 2000. New species of Orthocephalus and Myrmecophyes from Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan (Heteroptera: Miridae). Zoosystematica Rossica 8: 301 - 305." type="journal article" year="2000">Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). A single species has been collected from the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5B10FD61B08EFD60" box="[1309,1437,718,739]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5D37FD42B6F0FC81" authorityName="Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner" authorityYear="2000" box="[826,995,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trispiculus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37FD42B6F0FC81" box="[826,995,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">My. trispiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the asterid 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5B3FFD42B03EFCA2" authority="(Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner, 2000)" baseAuthorityName="Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terrae-albae">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5B3FFD42B6D1FCA3" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Artemisia terrae-albae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5DDEFCA4B035FCA2" author="Drapolyuk IS &amp; Kerzhner IM" box="[979,1318,779,801]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="301 - 305" refId="ref43521" refString="Drapolyuk IS, Kerzhner IM. 2000. New species of Orthocephalus and Myrmecophyes from Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan (Heteroptera: Miridae). Zoosystematica Rossica 8: 301 - 305." type="journal article" year="2000">Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner, 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="C6C30320FFD1FFDE5B33FCA4B082FCA2" box="[1342,1425,779,801]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="21.[144,208,200,219]" captionText="Table 1. Host plant records for the Halticini" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD1FFDE5D37FCE7B163FBD0" blockId="60.[826,1442,840,1903]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37FCE7B14AFCDE" box="[826,1113,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DBEFCE7B14AFCDE" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[947,1113,840,861]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Myrmecophyes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is arguably the most convincing ant mimetic genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A97FCC8B011FCFE" baseAuthorityName="Schuh" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1178,1282,871,893]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
. Based on its mymecomorphy, Carvalho (1952, 1955, 1958) erroneously placed the genus in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A9DFC0BB000FC39" box="[1168,1299,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pilophorini">Pilophorini</taxonomicName>
. Many characters contradict this assessment (e.g. tall genae, structure of the male and female genitalia) – and in any case several other 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A4DFBAFB1B6FB95" baseAuthorityName="Schuh" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1088,1189,1024,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
are also ant mimics – leading 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D95FBB0B151FBB7" author="Wagner E" box="[920,1090,1054,1076]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="230 - 242" refId="ref50655" refString="Wagner E. 1955. Bemerkungen zum System der Miridae (Hem. Het.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, N. F. 2: 230 - 242." type="book chapter" year="1955">Wagner (1955)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5A8CFBB0B008FBB6" author="Schuh RT" box="[1153,1307,1055,1077]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 332" refId="ref48926" refString="Schuh RT. 1974. The Orthotylinae and Phylinae (Hemiptera: Miridae) of South Africa with a phylogenetic analysis of the ant-mimetic tribes of the two subfamilies for the world. Entomologica Americana 47: 1 - 332." type="journal article" year="1974">Schuh (1974)</bibRefCitation>
to transfer the genus to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5A09FB92B17FFBD0" baseAuthorityName="Schuh" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1028,1132,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD1FFDE5D5EFBF3B13AF955" blockId="60.[826,1442,840,1903]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D5EFBF3B146FBF1" author="Schuh RT &amp; Lattin JD" box="[851,1109,1116,1138]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref49067" refString="Schuh RT, Lattin JD. 1980. Myrmecophyes oregonensis, a new species of Halticini (Hemiptera, Miridae) from the western United States. American Museum Novitates, 2697: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Schuh &amp; Lattin (1980)</bibRefCitation>
provided a brief summary of the genus. The most recent works on 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5AF6FBD5B0B2FB0C" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[1275,1441,1146,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5AF6FBD5B0B2FB0C" box="[1275,1441,1146,1167]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Myrmecophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5DC9FB36B1B7FB2C" author="Drapolyuk IS" box="[964,1188,1177,1199]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="125 - 135" refId="ref43463" refString="Drapolyuk IS. 1989. Species of the genus Myrmecophyes Fieb. (Heteroptera: Miridae) from the Caucasus. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 18: 125 - 135." type="journal article" year="1989">Drapolyuk’s (1989)</bibRefCitation>
description of three new species and key to the species of the Caucasus, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D61FB79B1C3FB6F" author="Drapolyuk IS &amp; Kerzhner IM" box="[876,1232,1238,1260]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="301 - 305" refId="ref43521" refString="Drapolyuk IS, Kerzhner IM. 2000. New species of Orthocephalus and Myrmecophyes from Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan and Turkmenistan (Heteroptera: Miridae). Zoosystematica Rossica 8: 301 - 305." type="journal article" year="2000">Drapolyuk &amp; Kerzhner’s (2000)</bibRefCitation>
description of two new species from 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFD1FFDE5A06FB5AB18BFA88" box="[1035,1176,1269,1291]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
. The most comprehensive work remains 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5A10FABCB1ABFAA9" author="Bykov AA" box="[1053,1208,1299,1322]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="495 - 501" refId="ref42447" refString="Bykov AA. 1971. Mirid bugs of the genus Myrmecophyes Fieb. (Heteroptera, Miridae) in the fauna of the Tien-Shan and the Pamir-Alai. Entomological Review 50: 495 - 501." type="journal article" year="1971">Bykov (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, which as 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5B36FABCB6C1FACB" author="Schuh RT &amp; Lattin JD" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref49067" refString="Schuh RT, Lattin JD. 1980. Myrmecophyes oregonensis, a new species of Halticini (Hemiptera, Miridae) from the western United States. American Museum Novitates, 2697: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Schuh &amp; Lattin (1980)</bibRefCitation>
note, omitted nine previously described species from its key and lacks a formal diagnosis. Thus, the most recent diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5AD0FAC0B090FA07" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[1245,1411,1391,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5AD0FAC0B090FA07" box="[1245,1411,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Myrmecophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is that of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5D98FA21B152FA27" author="Wagner E" box="[917,1089,1422,1444]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 423" refId="ref50943" refString="Wagner E. 1973. Die Miridae Hahn, 1831, des Mittelmeerraumes und der Makaronesischen Inseln (Hemiptera, Heteroptera). Entomologishe Abhandlungen 39: 1 - 423." type="journal article" year="1973">Wagner (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, which has been found by us and others (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFD1FFDE5A09FA03B01DFA40" author="Schuh RT &amp; Lattin JD" box="[1028,1294,1452,1475]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref49067" refString="Schuh RT, Lattin JD. 1980. Myrmecophyes oregonensis, a new species of Halticini (Hemiptera, Miridae) from the western United States. American Museum Novitates, 2697: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Schuh &amp; Lattin, 1980</bibRefCitation>
) to be both inadequate and inaccurate. Contrary to Wagner, not all species have white markings on the hemelytra, not all species exhibit a macropterous form, the first two abdominal segments are not constricted to form a waist – in fact, only occasionally is the second abdominal segment constricted, whereas in many species the abdomen remains relatively broad at its base – and the opening of the pygophore is not directed downwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD1FFDE5D5EF971B0B2F8EC" blockId="60.[826,1442,840,1903]" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">
The structure of the ductus seminis and secondary gonopore of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DECF952B194F891" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[993,1159,1789,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5DECF952B194F891" box="[993,1159,1789,1810]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Myrmecophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5D37F8B3B682F8B2" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1858" box="[826,913,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Anapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5D37F8B3B682F8B2" box="[826,913,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Anapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD1FFDE5DDFF8B3B171F8B2" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1875" box="[978,1122,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Euryopicoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD1FFDE5DDFF8B3B171F8B2" box="[978,1122,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="618">Euryopicoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In particular, in all three genera the distal portion of the ductus seminis lacks flexible sclerotized ribbing. This similarity is reflected
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD0FFDF5D91FF2BB09EFF1A" blockId="61.[924,1421,129,153]" box="[924,1421,129,153]" pageId="61" pageNumber="619">
THE 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD0FFDF5DD1FF2CB02CFF1B" authority="OF THE WORLD" authorityName="OF THE WORLD" box="[988,1343,131,153]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">HALTICINI OF THE WORLD</taxonomicName>
619
</paragraph>
