<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFD0FFDF5E9DFA7DB4E8F93D" blockId="61.[144,759,1490,1726]" pageId="61" pageNumber="619">
in the close relationship between these genera (as well as 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD0FFDF5EF5FA5FB459F986" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[248,330,1520,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Labops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD0FFDF5EF5FA5FB459F986" box="[248,330,1520,1541]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="619">Labops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD0FFDF5F98FA5FB706F986" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1890" box="[405,533,1520,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Scirtetellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD0FFDF5F98FA5FB706F986" box="[405,533,1520,1541]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="619">Scirtetellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) identified in our phylogenetic results. It should be noted that although the two species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFD0FFDF5F8FF982B73BF9C1" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[386,552,1581,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Myrmecophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFD0FFDF5F8FF982B73BF9C1" box="[386,552,1581,1602]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="619">Myrmecophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included in our phylogenetic analysis do not form a monophyletic group, we consider this to be an artefact of our small taxon sample for the genus as well as reflective of the limits of our character dataset.
</paragraph>
